&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;*********£2500 ‘Golden Hello’ Payment**********&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Apply now and If you are successfully recruited you will receive £2500- does not apply to current HIOW NHS Staff&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;SHFT are an equal opportunities employer and welcome applications from all who believe they fit the essential requirements for this role regardless of their race, sex, disability, religion/belief, sexual orientation or age.**However exemption is claimed under the Equality Act 2010 Part 1 Schedule 9 and applications can only be accepted from males due to the care needs of the MALE residents/patients**&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for a male practitioner to join our dynamic and recovery focused team. This would be a great developmental opportunity for a band 5 looking to broaden their experience within mental health. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will play an important role in delivering excellent care for our service users, and working as part of the team to provide the right support and assistance to our service users in their recovery. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Leading and contributing in the process of planning and coordinating service user care and undertaking interventions in line with agreed care plan.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Delivering higher level intensity community interventions as part of the integrated Shared Care model&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Formulating care plans in line with assessed need&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in a manner which is helpful to the service user and the referrer, based on principles of recovery, personalisation and choice.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working with individuals in the least restrictive manner possible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Deputising for the Team Leader as required.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working in a service which may include some evening, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will have previous experience in the effective and positive management of people with mental health needs and will be able to evidence effective team working and leadership skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;span&gt;Ability to drive and use of a car for work purpose is essential in this role.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are located close to Bournemouth and Southampton, with great transportation links to London and Winchester by road and rail, as well as having the beautiful New Forest National Park on our door step.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Our Trust offers continuous development for all of our staff, as well as regular supervision and annual appraisal, to ensure you achieve your personal goals and assist you in personal and professional development. Regular support from your line manager is also provided to ensure you have the opportunity to develop your skills further.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information, please contact Leanne Ballantyne – Team Manager or Natalie Evans on 02380 868886. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
